Vendor management becomes inefficient when onboarding, purchase order updates, and supplier communication are handled through disconnected routines.

## A coordinated workflow

1. Standardized vendor onboarding checklist
2. Clear PO ownership and status updates
3. Structured supplier communication templates
4. Escalation rules for delays and missing data

## Operational benefits

- Fewer coordination gaps
- Better supplier response consistency
- Faster issue resolution

Reliable procurement execution depends on clear process structure more than ad-hoc effort.
